text.section:
When a cooperative is dissolved, its assets shall be distributed in the following manner and order:
By paying its debts and expenses;
By returning to the members the lesser of par value or book value of their shares, their membership capital, or allocated equity;
By returning to the subscribers the lesser of par value or book value of amounts paid on their subscriptions;
By returning to eligible patrons the lesser of par value or book value of the amount of net savings credited to their accounts toward the purchase of shares or membership; and
By distributing any surplus as a gift to another cooperative or to a nonprofit, tax-exempt enterprise.
